SIMPLE: pipe_line
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pipe line
<hw>pipe line</hw></mhw>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
line of pipe with pumping machinery and apparatus for conveying liquids,
gases, or finely divided solids, such as petroleum or natural gas,
between distant points.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def><mark>fig.</mark> an information channel direct from
the source.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the set of stages and processes from the invention
or design of a product to its ultimate use, production, or commercial
sale. Used commonly in the phrase <col><b>in the pipeline</b></col>,
<it>i. e.</it> still in preparation or under development.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pipe-line</ent>⟦br⟧
